Pour @water{300%ml}(cold) into a #medium pot{} with a tight-fitting #lid{}.
Add @salt{to taste}.
Stir in the @rice{150%g} and bring to the boil.

Once boiling, lower the heat to medium, cover, and cook for ~{10%minutes}.

Once cooked, remove the #pot{} from the heat.
Keep covered for ~{10%minutes} or until ready to serve (the rice will continue
to cook in its own steam).

Trim the tip of the @broccoli{1}. Cut head into small florets and stem into
2cm pieces.

Peel and grate the @garlic{1}(peeled and grated) (or use a #garlic press{}).

Roughly chop the @coriander{5%g} (stalks and all).

Halve the @chilli{1} and discard the core and seeds. Finely chop.

In a #small bowl{}, create the katsu sauce by mixing the @honey{2%sachets},
@korma curry paste{1%sachet} and @aioli{1%sachet}.

Place a pan over medium-high heat with a drizzle of @oil{to taste}.
Once hot, add the broccoli and fry for ~{2-3%minutes}.

Stir in the garlic, lower heat to medium and cook for ~{1%minute}.

Add a splash of water and cover with a lid or some #foil{}. Cook until tender,
~{4-5%minutes}.

Remove from the pan, set aside and cover to keep warm.

> TIP: Reserve pan for later use.

Beat @egg{1} in a #medium bowl{}.
Add the @breadcrumbs{1%pack} to another #bowl{}. Season with @salt{to taste} and
@pepper{to taste}.

Place a hand on top of the @Irish chicken breast{320%g}. Slice horizontally to
make two thin steaks. Season with salt and pepper.

Dip the chicken in the egg, then the breadcrumbs.

> IMPORTANT: Wash hands and equipment after handling raw chicken.

> TIP: Notice a stronger smell from your chicken? This is normal due to
> packaging used to keep it fresh.

Return the pan to high heat with just enough @oil{to taste} to cover the bottom.

Once hot, carefully lay the chicken into the pan.

Reduce the heat to medium-high and fry until golden brown and cooked through,
~{8-10%minutes}.

> IMPORTANT: Chicken is cooked when no longer pink in the middle. Cook in
> batches if the pan is too crowded.

Turn every 2-3 mins, adjusting the heat if necessary.

> TIP: Allow the oil to heat for 2-3 mins before adding the chicken.

Remove the chicken from the #oven{} and thinly slice.

Fluff up the rice with a #fork{} and divide between plates.

Top with the crumbed chicken and pan-fried broccoli.

Drizzle the katsu sauce over the chicken and rice.

Finish with a scattering of chopped coriander and chilli (use less if you
don't like spice).